contents.value:
```hcl
output "instance_ip" {
  value = aws_instance.web.public_ip
}
```
**output** blocks expose values from your module, visible after `terraform apply`.

```hcl
data "aws_ami" "ubuntu" {
  most_recent = true
  filter {
    name   = "name"
    values = ["ubuntu/images/*"]
  }
}
```
**data** sources read existing infrastructure. Referenced as `data.type.name.attribute`.

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}
```
**provider** configures the connection to a cloud/service API. Each resource type belongs to a provider.

```hcl
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket = "my-state"
    key    = "terraform.tfstate"
    region = "us-east-1"
  }
}
```
**backend** stores Terraform state remotely. Enables team collaboration and state locking.

```hcl
dynamic "ingress" {
  for_each = var.ports
  content {
    from_port = ingress.value
    to_port   = ingress.value
  }
}
```
**dynamic** blocks generate repeated nested blocks from collections. Avoids repetitive configuration.
